# Windows batch files (.cmd/.bat) here use CP949 (Korean ANSI) + CRLF so that
# Korean Windows cmd.exe can parse the Korean script filenames correctly.
# Treat them as binary so git never touches the bytes — no autocrlf conversion,
# no encoding normalization. If you edit these files, save them in ANSI/CP949
# with CRLF endings (Notepad "ANSI" encoding on Korean Windows is CP949).
*.cmd   binary
*.bat   binary
